cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Forge in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "Forge: A Local-First, Multi-Agent Software-Engineering Runtime"
abstract: >-
  Forge is a local-first, multi-agent software-engineering runtime that runs
  Claude Code / Codex-style agentic coding workflows entirely on a developer's
  own machine. It supports local model backends (Ollama, llama.cpp, vLLM,
  LM Studio) alongside optional cloud providers (Anthropic, OpenAI), and
  ships eighteen sandboxed tools, a permission-gated execution model, and a
  REPL plus web UI dashboard in a single Node.js CLI.
